    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0103"/>
        		<head>Jim to Mlle. Marcelle Guerin <date value="1915-06-18">June 18th 1915</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1915-06-18">June 18th 1915</date></dateline>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            I have just heard that
            your hero, D..D.L. McGrew,
            the complete Adonis I
            described to you, and who
            you wanted to meet, has
            left for the States.  I 
            now breathe easier and
            hope for less divided thoughts.
            </p><p>
            As a special favor Ned
            Salisbury or chief took
            me on a flying trip to
            visit the tent squad.  We 
            coursed thru [sic] Gaul and
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0104" n="[p.2]"/>
            
            on beyond and nearing
            Pagney we beheld, sequestered
            in a most charmingly
            peaceful spot, between a
            village church and a 
            winding stream, the various
            and sundry shaped canvases
            of the far famed Tent Squad.
            The conductuers were in
            comfortable summer garb
            and some wore straw hats.
            I tried to recollect where I
            had pictured just such
            a thing before and then 
            remembered that one always
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0105" n="[p.3]"/>
            
            imagined such an outfit
            when reading advertisements
            of a summer camp “for
            respectable youths of
            genteel parentage”  Not a
            single blesse’ have they
            nor do they know their
            prospects.  Of course we
            were met with a great
            reception.  In from the
            front stuff, you know
            and they asked us a
            hundred and one questions.
            Old Doty was there.
            </p><p>
            We’ve done so well here
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0106" n="[p.4]"/>
            
            that we’re to be given
            the work of an adjacent
            division as well as the
            one we are attached to
            at present.
            </p><p>
            Our staff car leaves on
            Monday or Tuesday (21st or 22nd)
            and a letter turned in at 
            the office would be awfully 
            welcome.
            </p><p>
            I’ve missed you terribly
            all day.  Don’t understand
            why it should intensify
            suddenly at times.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <signed>Jim</signed>
        		</closer>
        		
            
